sdgfetch and sdgtip run on every new terminal window
tipme shows a random SDG-OS tip from any terminal
eza aliases: ls, la, ll, lt give colorful directory listings
zoxide lets you cd <partial> to jump to any directory
find uses fzf with bat preview for fuzzy file search
plz re-runs the last command with sudo
Ghostty pane splits with Alt+Arrow keys
cmdhist searches your command history with fzf
Ctrl+R reloads the Ghostty config
microfind opens a fuzzy-selected file in micro editor
cowtip shows a random tip with cowsay and lolcat
